{"ts":"2026-06-27T18:02:12.386Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Agent Initialization**\n\nOkay, I'm examining how the page component initializes its agent data. Currently, it uses a `useState` hook with a static `INITIAL_AGENTS` list. But I've realized this needs to connect to CRUD APIs. I'll need to initialize `agents` more dynamically to accommodate API calls.\n\n\n**Refining Initialization Logic**\n\nI'm now thinking I'll initialize `agents` as an empty array `[]` on mount, then populate it dynamically. I'll load agent data from `/api/v1/ai-operations` using `apiClient.aiOperations.list()` and map the API response to a `RichAgentOperation`. I am also now researching project name lookups by project ID, which is critical for making `UNIQUE_PROJECTS` constant more dynamic.\n\n\n**Implementing Create/Edit Modals**\n\nI'm working on adding create/edit modals for operational agents. I've defined states for modal visibility (`isCreateModalOpen`, `isEditModalOpen`), the edited agent form (`editAgentForm`), loading status (`loading`), and error handling (`error`). I'm also planning the form fields: name, project, tenant client, agent type, operational status, and governance severity.\n\n\n"}}
